# ── Environment contract ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# `astro.config.mjs` resolves public build values from the shell first, then
# `wrangler.jsonc`. Those values drive Astro's site, canonical URLs, sitemap,
# JSON-LD, and indexability together. For a deployed build, pass the values in
# the build environment (or keep `wrangler.jsonc` in sync); never enable
# indexing without the final HTTPS origin.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Public: canonical origin (e.g. https://example.com). Preview builds should use the workers.dev URL.
PUBLIC_SITE_URL="http://localhost:4321"

# Public: app origin (e.g. https://app.example.com). Used for "Sign in" / "Go to app" links.
PUBLIC_APP_URL="http://localhost:3001"

# Public: Cloudflare Turnstile site key for the Lite Check. Leave unset while
# PUBLIC_APP_URL is absent and the scanner is intentionally unavailable.
PUBLIC_TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY=""

# Public: monitored mailbox rendered in legal/abuse copy before indexing.
PUBLIC_ABUSE_EMAIL=""

# Public: X/Twitter profile URL. Leave unset to hide the link entirely.
# PUBLIC_X_URL="https://x.com/your-handle"

# Public: set to "true" only on the real production domain after founder go-live.
PUBLIC_INDEXABLE="false"

# Public: PostHog project key. Leave unset to disable analytics entirely.
# PUBLIC_POSTHOG_KEY="phc_..."

# Public: PostHog host. Default is the EU endpoint.
PUBLIC_POSTHOG_HOST="https://eu.i.posthog.com"

# Secret: random 32+ character salt for ip_hash.
# In local dev wrangler reads secrets from `.dev.vars` (not `.env`). Copy `.dev.vars.example` and update it there.
# WAITLIST_IP_SALT=""
